<h2 id="head-258dad55cfea1ed90573f315bd20393b2c10d57b">Legal Issues</h2>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Aren't those modules based on modern books, games, and/or television series going to run into the same type of problem that was had with <a href="./PernAngband">PernAngband</a>? 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: Any developer would have to become familiar with the relevant law.  In the US, a parody is allowed, so a game that made a parody of the given work would be fine.   Whether the above would be entertaining in parody form is another question, though. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Hm, I can understand the distinction, but in an odd way that's going straight past law right into Zen koan land. <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile.png" alt=":-)" height="15" width="15"> No, I'm not making fun, just pondering. So do you think it might be a problem? 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: Not for us.  If there's a legal problem it'll be for whoever distributes the module, and the local laws will apply to the author.  Given the wide geographic distribution of ToME's players, we can't generalize the laws relevant to these module ideas. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Works for me. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NerdanelVampire">NerdanelVampire</a>: By the way, it looks like someone could make a Pernband module without getting sued since Anne <a class="nonexistent" href="./McCaffrey">McCaffrey</a> has <a class="external" href=".www.annemccaffrey.org/fan-fiction-rules.html">changed her mind</a>. I wouldn't make or play such a module though. I have zero interest in Pern and have liked none of <a class="nonexistent" href="./McCaffrey">McCaffrey</a>'s stories I have read. 
</p>
<h2 id="head-0be8c5f4a493a729741e24ab478637b07d047072">Module Concepts</h2>
<p>
<a href="./Modules_2fTime_20Travel">/Time Travel</a> 
</p>
<h2 id="head-ff11f0da0a4cd245270f188d8a7299b4084d0328">Chatter</h2>
<p>
<a href="./NerdanelVampire">NerdanelVampire</a>: What is the difference between a module idea and a module concept? Should I move Hero Pingis to concepts? 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: I placed Time Travel in Module Concepts because it's a general discussion of game concepts that modules can use, rather than  an idea for a specific module. 
</p>
